snippet.textDisplay: For those who really know football, it's not really hard to figure out what Pep did and why he did it. Jesus was on the left to keep Carvajal in check and give him problems on the other end. The best chance in the 1st half fell to Jesus on the left side. Then inserting a fresh Sterling on the left give different problems for the RB. Both goals were created in that zone. It wasn't by accident. Pep's plan worked and he looks like a genius again. And KDB showed why he is the best midfielder in the world.

snippet.textDisplay:
Hmmm i feel that the pundits clearly don't understand the thought process for those decisions made. If Pep sees that playing wide is the solution, then the logical thing to do is let them do so by getting men wide which will include Gabby and Rihad. Im not saying its the perfect solution, but again, the thought process that came to that decision. The chain effect must take full cycle, u cannot attempt to play wide while getting men in central areas. Its also a possession based decision as well.

In the end, Gab beat RM's Ramos to get that goal and also effectively eliminated him from next match with 2 away goals. I'll say thats well controlled success. And we all know Pep is about control, not domination. Its could only be the after effects of good control but not above it.
